    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Entomobrya, habitus of some species.A, E. multisetis sp. nov.; B–C, E. kremenitsai sp. nov.; D–F, E. hirsutothorax sp. nov. (bar 0.25mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5030466/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030474>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Entomobrya kremenitsai sp. nov. A, head macrochaetotaxy; B, AntIV tip, showing the apical vesicle, the bifurcate pin chaeta, and the special organite; C, distal area of AntIII showing the sensory organ; D, labral papillae; E, claw and empodium; F, ThII dorsal macrochaetotaxy; G, AbdII–III dorsal macrochaetotaxy; H, AbdIV dorsal macrochaetotaxy (scale bars: A, F–H, 0.1mm; B–D, 0.01 mm; E, 0.025 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5030474/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

